This creates a comprehensive about page featuring:
Hero Section:
Animated EMS/Mangekyō Sharingan logo with pulse effects
"I alone am the translator of all manga" tagline
Version badge with channel indicator (Stable/Beta/Dev)
Live Statistics:
Animated counters for pages translated, OCR accuracy, active sessions
Persistent stats fetched from background service worker
Update Manager:
Automatic update checking on load
Manual check button with status indicators
Inline changelog display for available updates
One-click installation trigger
The Journey Timeline:
Visual roadmap from "Awakening" (v1.0) → "Mangekyō" (v2.0) → "Eternal Mangekyō" (current) → "Rinnegan" (v3.0 roadmap)
Thematic progression matching the extension's visual metaphor
Credits Section:
Team attribution with role-based cards
Special thanks to scanlation community and Kishimoto
Open source license accordion (Tesseract.js, TensorFlow.js, Sharp, GPL-3.0)
Resources:
GitHub, Documentation, Discord, and Feedback links
Modal-based feedback form with diagnostic log attachment option
Technical Debug Panel:
Collapsible system information (Extension ID, Chrome version, platform, Service Worker status, permissions)
One-click copy for support requests
Footer:
Responsible use disclaimer supporting official releases
Copyright and attribution
The page maintains the Naruto visual theme throughout while providing practical functionality for update management and user support.